          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1720449080049-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the basa is cooking, zest<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>(try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>non-zested lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1720449088831-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1720449088831-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1720449088831-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1720449088831-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1720449088831-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the basa is nearly cooked through, add your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[125ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span><strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to the pan along with the juice of the <strong>zested lemon </strong>(reserve the wedges for garnish!)</p><p>Season very generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until the spinach is wilted, you are left with a loose sauce and your fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1720449089661-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1720449089661-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1720449089661-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1720449089661-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1720449089661-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>lemony smoked basa & spinach gluten free linguine</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1720449095056-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1720449095056-x400.jpg",
